Eskom CEO André de Ruyter said the ongoing outages are necessary to catch up with long overdue maintenance. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom CEO André de Ruyter says the power utility is experiencing high unplanned capacity loss. He says there are adequate reserves to last the power utility until Monday evening. Eskom will implement stage 2 power cuts from 9pm until 5am on Tuesday. READ: Eskom to implement Stage 2 blackouts from 9pm This is to conserve and replenish emergency reserves. Meanwhile, de Ruyter says underperforming executives will face the consequences. Those concerned will be notified soon. Eskom CEO André de Ruyter says the power utility is experiencing high unplanned capacity loss. He says there are adequate reserves to last the power utility until early this evening. #Eskom will implement stage 2 power cuts from 9pm tonight until 5am tomorrow. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/wqnfas2kzR